content:
the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation through NPM registry.
Install: npm install -g codefresh
Install a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: npm install -g codefresh
Update to a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@${VERSION}

 Description Create a config context.
Command codefresh create context config &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a config. codefresh create context config my-config -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

 Description Delete a helm release from a kubernetes cluster.
Command codefresh delete-release &lt;name&gt;
Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --cluster -c  Run on cluster. required   --timeout -t 300 time in seconds to wait for any individual kubernetes operation (like Jobs for hooks) (default 300)   --purge -p  remove the release from the store and make its name free for later use (default true)   --detach -d  Run pipeline and print build ID   --no-hooks --nh  prevent hooks from running during deletion   --tiller-namespace -n kube-system namespace where is tiller running ( helm 2 only )   --namespace --ns default namespace where is chart located ( helm 3 )    Examples Delete release &ldquo;my-release&rdquo; from cluster &ldquo;my-cluster&rdquo; codefresh delete-release my-release --cluster my-cluster

 Description Rollback a helm release from a kubernetes cluster.
Command codefresh rollback-release &lt;name&gt;
Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --cluster -c  Run on cluster. required   --revision -t  revision number. required   --tiller-namespace -n kube-system prevent hooks from running during deletion   --namespace --ns default prevent hooks from running during deletion   --detach -d  Run pipeline and print build ID    Examples rollback release &ldquo;my-release&rdquo; from cluster &ldquo;my-cluster&rdquo; codefresh rollback my-release --cluster my-cluster --revision 1

 Description Integrate a standard container registry into Codefresh.
Command codefresh create registry standard &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Registry name    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --username   Username to access the docker registry. required   --password   Password to access the docker registry. required   --domain   Domain to access the docker registry. required   --behind-firewall   Set if the registry is behind a firewall

the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation using YARN.
Install: yarn global add codefresh
Install a specific version: yarn global add codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: yarn global upgrade codefresh
Update to a specific version: yarn global upgrade codefresh@{VERSION}

 Description Create a resource from a file, directory or url
Supported resources: &lsquo;context&rsquo;
&lsquo;step-type&rsquo;
&lsquo;project&rsquo;
&lsquo;pipeline&rsquo;
&lsquo;annotation&rsquo;.
Command codefresh create
Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource

 Description Create a composition.
Command codefresh create composition &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh create com &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of composition    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource   --compose-file -c  Path to docker-compose.yaml file to use to create the resource. required   --variable -v  Variables list   --advanced -a  Advanced composition    Examples Creating a composition using a docker-compose.yml file codefresh create composition NAME --compose-file ./docker-compose.yml
Defining composition variables codefresh create composition NAME --compose-file ./docker-compose.yml -v key1=value1 -v key2=value2

 Description Create a team.
You can create a new team specifying only name of team or specify path to json file for include extended options
Possible fields in file:
name - team name (specifying name in file will rewrite name specified as command argument) users - array of users id for that team tags - array of tag names.
Command codefresh create teams &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh create team &lt;name&gt;
codefresh create tm &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of team    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource   --user-id -u  undefined   --tag -t  undefined    Examples Creating a team specifying only team name codefresh create team NAME
Creating a team using a file to specify additional options codefresh create team NAME -f [pathToFile]

 Description Create a secret context.
Command codefresh create context secret &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a secret. codefresh create context secret my-secret -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

You can run the CLI using our official docker image which is published to Dockerhub
Pull the latest version: docker pull codefresh/cli
Pull a specific version: docker pull codefresh/cli:${VERSION}

 Description Delete a cluster.
Command codefresh delete cluster &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete clusters &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Cluster name. required    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information    Examples Delete cluster NAME codefresh delete cluster NAME

 Description Delete a composition.
Command codefresh delete composition &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete com &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Composition name    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource    Examples Delete a composition codefresh delete composition NAME

 Description Delete an environment.
Command codefresh delete environment &lt;id&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete env &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Environment id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information    Examples Delete environment ID codefresh delete environment ID

 Description Delete registry from Codefresh.
Command codefresh delete registry &lt;ID&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     ID   ID of a registry to delete    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information

 Description Create a secret-yaml context.
Command codefresh create context secret-yaml &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list

 Description Test a helm release.
Command codefresh test-release &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Release name. required    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --cluster   Run on cluster. required   --tiller-namespace -n kube-system namespace where is tiller running ( helm 2 only )   --namespace --ns default namespace where is chart located ( helm 3 )   --timeout  300 time in seconds to wait for any individual kubernetes operation (like Jobs for hooks) (default 300)   --detach -d  Run pipeline and print build ID   --cleanup   delete test pods upon completion (default false)

 Description Patch Codefresh token.
Update token name or scopes using token id. Id can be retrieved using &ldquo;get&rdquo; command.
Command codefresh patch tokens &lt;id&gt;
Aliases codefresh patch token &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   token id. required    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --name   token name or ids   --scope -s  token names or ids    Examples Update token name codefresh patch token [token_id] --name new-name
Set token scopes to &ldquo;pipeline&rdquo;, &ldquo;project&rdquo; codefresh patch token [token_id] -s pipeline -s project

 Description Set the current active authentication context.
Command codefresh auth use-context &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   a context-name that exists in cfconfig file    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --cfconfig   Custom path for authentication contexts config file (default: &lsquo;/root/.cfconfig&rsquo;)   --help   Print help information    Examples Set active authentication context to NAME codefresh auth use-context NAME

 Description Create a yaml context.
Command codefresh create context yaml &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --variable -v  Variables list

 Description Annotate an image.
Annotating an image gives the ability to add extra context on your already existing images.
Command codefresh annotate image &lt;id&gt;
Aliases codefresh annotate img &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Docker image full name or id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --label -l  annotations to add to the image    Examples Annotate an image with a single label codefresh annotate image 2dfacdaad466 -l coverage=75%
Annotate an image with multiple labels codefresh annotate image 2dfacdaad466 -l coverage=75% -l tests_passed=true

 Description Replace a resource from a file, directory or url
Supported resources: &lsquo;Context&rsquo;
&lsquo;Pipeline&rdquo;
&lsquo;Step-type&rsquo;.
Command codefresh replace
Options    Option Alias Default Description     --help   Print help information   --filename -f  Filename or directory of spec files use to create the resource   --skip-trigger-validation   Set to true to skip validation (for pipeline replace)

 Create Config Context codefresh create context config &lt;name&gt;
Create a config context.
Create Secret Context codefresh create context secret &lt;name&gt;
Create a secret context.
Create Secret-Yaml Context codefresh create context secret-yaml &lt;name&gt;
Create a secret-yaml context.
Create Yaml Context codefresh create context yaml &lt;name&gt;
Create a yaml context.

 Get Registries codefresh get registry
Get an array of accounts registries.
Standard codefresh create registry standard &lt;name&gt;
Integrate a standard container registry into Codefresh.
Delete Registry codefresh delete registry &lt;ID&gt;
Delete registry from Codefresh.

 kubernetes-runtime codefresh create context secret-store kubernetes-runtime &lt;name&gt;
Create a secret-store Kubernetes-Runtime context.
Create a secret store to use hybrid runtime to access K8S secret/configmap and use it as secret store.
kubernetes codefresh create context secret-store kubernetes &lt;name&gt;
Create a secret-store Kubernetes context.
Secret-Store context are used during pipeline execution as API to resolve variables that are parse of Codefresh.

 Delete Helm Release codefresh delete-release &lt;name&gt;
Delete a helm release from a kubernetes cluster.
Rollback Helm Release codefresh rollback-release &lt;name&gt;
Rollback a helm release from a kubernetes cluster.
Set Helm config codefresh set-helm-config &lt;cluster&gt;
Set Helm config.
Install or Upgrade Helm Chart codefresh install-chart
Install or upgrade a Helm chart Repository flag can be either absolute url or saved repository in Codefresh.
Promote Helm Release codefresh helm-promotion
Promote a Helm release in another environment.
Test Helm Release codefresh test-release &lt;name&gt;
Test a helm release.
